ere,"},{"kind":"text","text":"day: (Fr, S, O, K:) or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently-hot"},{"kind":"text","text":"day: (Fr, K:) and the former is in like manner applied to a night ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolap","text_ar":"لَيْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and ↓ the latter signifies also a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cold, and very cloudy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which nothing is seen of the sky."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l- 'Alà, L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Fr","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B9%D8%B5%D9%8A%D8%A8/","headword_ar":"عصيب","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_39","lexicon_en":"ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAbbās, Gharīb al-Qurʾān fī Shiʿr al-ʿArab, also known as Masāʾil Nāfiʿ b. al-Azraq (d. 687 CE)","lexicon_ar":"غريب القرآن في شعر العرب لعبد الله بن عباس","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=94301#990f4d","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ع ص ب [عصيب]</span><br><span>قال: يا ابن عباس: أخبرني عن قول الله عزّ وجلّ: يَوْمٌ عَصِيبٌ .</span><br><span>قال: يوم شديد.</span><br><span>قال: وهل تعرف العرب ذلك؟</span><br><span>قال: نعم، أما سمعت الشاعر وهو يقول:</span><br><span>هم ضربوا قوانس خيل حجر </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> بجنب الرده في يوم عصيب </span>"}]}}